### How to Measure a Person's Height (for Prognostication)

**Step 1 — Measure Body Length:**

- Measure from the **big toe of the foot** to the **hairline on the forehead**.

**Step 2 — Add One-Forth of Chest Circumference:**

- Measure the circumference of the body **at the chest**.
- Calculate **one-fourth** of this chest circumference.
- Add this value to the body length measured in Step 1.

**Step 3 — Measure Total in Own Finger-Breadths:**

- Convert the total length into **finger-breadths of the person’s own hand**.

**Step 4 — Interpret Results:**

- **108 finger-breadths** → will rule the whole world under one umbrella.
- **Different results** are indicated if the length is shorter or longer than 108 finger-breadths.

